Package musicSerialization

Klasse Artist

java.lang.Object
musicSerialization.Artist
Alle implementierten Schnittstellen:
Serializable
public class Artist extends Object implements Serializable
Represents a musical artist with associated metadata such as genres and web links.

This class is serializable and supports conversion to and from a semicolon-delimited string format.

  • Konstruktordetails

    • Artist

      public Artist(String name, int artistID, ArrayList<String> genres, String website, String lastFmUrl)
      Constructs a new Artist instance with the specified properties.
      Parameter:
      name - the name of the artist
      artistID - the unique identifier for the artist
      genres - a list of genres associated with the artist
      website - the artist's official website URL, or null if none
      lastFmUrl - the Last.fm profile URL for the artist

    • fromString

      public static Artist fromString(String data)
      Creates an Artist instance by parsing a semicolon-delimited string.

      Expected format: artistID;name;genre1,genre2;website;lastFmUrl

      Parameter:
      data - the semicolon-delimited artist data string
      Gibt zurück:
      a new Artist object populated from the data string
      Löst aus:
      IllegalArgumentException - if the data string is null, has an incorrect number of fields, or if the artistID cannot be parsed as an integer
